      "date": "2017-03-23T15:01:20Z",
      "sha": "added19e00a8e3717551c7aa12f34421dffc4a09",
      "message": "fix: don't append observations if finder has failed\n\nWithout this patch, the observations array size is increased by 2 even when\n`findInternal()` returns `false`.\n\nThe following patch would have solved the problem too, but it seemed\ncleaner to let `findInternal()` work on a temporary copy instead of\ntracking down and undoing all changes:\n\n    @@ -208,6 +208,9 @@ ROS_INFO_STREAM(\"looking for point \" << i);\n               isnan(rgbd.point.z))\n           {\n             ROS_ERROR_STREAM(\"checkerboard_finder: NAN point on geometrymsgs point \" << i);\n    +\n    +\t// undo the resize from above\n    +        msg->observations.resize(msg->observations.size() - 2);\n\n             return false;\n           }",
      "files_changed": 1,
      "additions": 6,
      "deletions": 1,
      "commit_type": "code"
    }
